Job#: 3014834

Job Description:

Seeking a Microbiologist to join a Biotech company in the greater Philadelphia area.

POSITION SUMMARY

The Microbiologist will perform routine environmental monitoring in a cleanroom environment and characterize and trend microbial recoveries for the program to support manufacturing operations.

Essential Functions:

Aseptically collect viable and non-viable samples from the manufacturing cleanrooms.

Participate in the Qualification and/or Validation of Microbiological methods and equipment.

Enumerate, isolate, and identify microbial recoveries.

Perform routine testing utilizing Microbiological Test Methods under cGMP Guidelines such as Bioburden, pH, Osmolality, and Endotoxin.

Report and participate in Out of Specification/Out of Trend Investigations.

Participate in Deviations, CAPA's, and other continuous improvement activities.

Draft/Revise SOPs, Reports and other documents using sound technical writing skills.

Participate in general laboratory cleaning and maintenance in support of a safe workspace.

Comply with cGxPs, SOPs, safety requirements, and all company policies.

POSITION QUALIFICATIONS

Competencies:

General understanding and demonstrated proficiencies in of some of the following different microbiological/analytical methods:

o Aseptic technique

o Cleanroom gowning

o Environmental Monitoring

o Microbial culture techniques

o Microbial staining techniques

o Brightfield microscopy

o Bioburden

o pH

o Osmolality

o Bacterial Endotoxin Test

o ELISA

Education and Experience:

Degree in Biology, Biochemistry, or Related Field

At least 1 year of related experience in a regulated environment.

Computer Skills:

Proficient in Microsoft Office products and performing microbiological statistical analysis using an appropriate software.

PHYSICAL DEMANDS

Occasionally lift up to 25 lbs.

Must be able to stand, squat, bend and walk frequently.

Other Physical Requirements:

Must wear appropriate Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) which include Lab Coat, Gloves, Safety Glasses. Must be able to aseptically gown for cleanroom entry and wear the attire for extended periods of time.

WORK ENVIRONMENT

Work is performed on-site in office and laboratory setting.

The noise level in the work environment is usually quiet in office settings and moderate in other situations.

Only local candidates will be considered.

Job Title: GPS Deploy - Senior Implementation Specialist, Service Delivery - US
Job Description:
Job#: 3014789

Job Description:

JOB TITLE: Senior Implementation Specialist, Service Delivery

DURATION: 6 MONTHS

LOCATION: REMOTE

PAY RATE: $51 - $61 HOURLY

Job Description:

Must have Skills :

Avamar, PowerProtect DD (Data Domain), Integrated Data Protection Appliance (IDPA), PowerProtect Data Manager (PPDM), and Data Protection Advisor (DPA).

Detailed Project Tasks:

Administer backup policies, schedules, and retention; configure and optimize Avamar datasets, client plug-ins, and PPDM protection policies for VMware, SQL Server, and Oracle workloads.

Manage Data Domain storage: MTree layout, cleaning schedules, replication (Collection/Directory), encryption, certificates, capacity planning, alerts, and software/firmware updates.

Implement and maintain SQL Server and Oracle backup/restore modules and agents for Avamar and PPDM; validate RMAN and VDI strategies; perform point-in-time and granular recoveries.

Monitor job health, performance, and capacity in PPDM, Avamar Activity/Policy views, and DPA dashboards; build custom DPA reports for SLA compliance, trends, and chargeback.

Troubleshoot end-to-end backup and restore failures across clients, network, and storage tiers; analyze logs (Avamar client/server, PPDM services, DDOS), and drive permanent fixes.

Execute DR tests and recovery runbooks; verify RPO/RTO; manage replication failover/failback for Avamar grids and DD endpoints.

Deliver hands-on training and knowledge transfer to the Sedgwick team: operations runbooks, SOPs, best practices, and tool-specific workshops (Avamar, DD, PPDM, DPA).

Coordinate with Networking and Data Center teams for connectivity, routing/VLANs, MTU/Jumbo Frames, DNS/NTP, and storage/iSCSI/FC prerequisites for new deployments.

Plan and execute Data Domain deployment projects with Dell: rack/stack, secure build, DDOS configuration, MTree design, replication topology, certificate management, and acceptance testing.

Integrate with ServiceNow for incident, change, and problem management; create KBs, maintain CMDB accuracy, and align with CAB and maintenance windows.

Use 1Password (or approved enterprise vault) to manage privileged credentials securely and enforce secrets hygiene across backup infrastructure.

Capacity and performance planning: forecast growth, right-size storage/compute, tune datasets/concurrency, dedupe/compression, and cleaning windows to meet SLAs.

Automation and scripting: streamline recurring tasks (policy updates, report exports, health checks), and standardize deployment/config baselines.

Vendor engagement: open and manage Dell service requests, collect diagnostics (sysinfos, logs), drive root cause analysis, and verify corrective actions.

Documentation: maintain architecture diagrams, inventories, runbooks, recovery procedures, and post-incident reports; provide weekly status and executive summaries.

On-call and escalation: provide L2/L3 support coverage, lead bridge calls, and coordinate cross-functional response for high-severity incidents.

Continuous improvement: assess environment health, recommend upgrades/migrations, optimize policies, and deprecate legacy workflows to reduce risk and cost.

Avamar, PowerProtect DD (Data Domain), Integrated Data Protection Appliance (IDPA), PowerProtect Data Manager (PPDM), and Data Protection Advisor (DPA).
